</paragraph>
<paragraph id="455F36E84A60E011FF0CFE99FB73FE62" blockId="12.[151,1437,261,936]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="7794EAFA4A60E011FF0CFE99FF71FEF1" box="[151,209,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<collectingRegion id="8724F80A4A60E011FF0CFE99FF71FEF1" box="[151,209,261,287]" country="Maldives" name="Maale" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Male</collectingRegion>
</emphasis>
. Head ochraceous with brownish tinge, frontal sutures brown. Eyes brown with greenish tinge and ocelli black. Face yellow with lateral margins of frontclypeus narrowly brown. Pronotum and mesonotum dark brown with posterior margins pale. Forewing brown with hyaline costal margin, venation darker. Thoracic sternites with large fuscous and ochraceous markings. Legs ochraceous, bases of setae dark (
<figureCitation id="DDDB2A6D4A60E011FB93FEEDFBC9FE62" box="[1032,1129,369,396]" captionStart="FIGURES 1" captionStartId="36.[151,264,1896,1921]" captionTargetBox="[177,1410,169,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[159,1428,166,1875]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURES 1 A–O. Habitus of Coelidiini species. A. Calodia deergha sp. nov., male; B. C. keralica sp. nov., male; C &amp; D. C. kodikanelensis Nielson, male and female; E. C. kumari sp. nov., male; F &amp; G. C. neofusca sp. nov., male and female; H &amp; I. C. ostenta (Distant), male and female; J. C. periyari sp. nov., male; K. C. subcrista Nielson, male; L. C. tridenta sp. nov., male; M. Glaberana acuta sp. nov., male; N &amp; O. G. khasiensis (Rao), male and female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366546/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Figs. 1 J</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="DDDB2A6D4A60E011FBEEFEEDFB37FE62" box="[1141,1175,369,396]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1897,1922]" captionTargetBox="[188,1409,181,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[164,1423,166,1884]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 4 A–O. Habitus of Coelidiini species, lateral view. A. Calodia deergha sp. nov., male; B. C. keralica sp. nov., male; C &amp; D. C. kodikanelensis Nielson, male and female; E. C. kumari sp. nov., male; F &amp; G. C. neofusca sp. nov., male and female; H &amp; I. C. ostenta (Distant), male and female; J. C. periyari sp. nov., male; K. C. subcrista Nielson, male; L. C. tridenta sp. nov., male; M. Glaberana acuta sp. nov., male; N &amp; O. G. khasiensis (Rao), male and female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366552/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">4 J</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="DDDB2A6D4A60E011FB38FEEEFB65FE62" box="[1187,1221,370,396]" captionStart="FIGURES 7" captionStartId="42.[151,264,1892,1917]" captionTargetBox="[175,1425,310,1744]" captionTargetId="figure@42.[151,1435,264,1750]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURES 7 A–P. Faces of Coelidiini species. A. Calodia deergha sp. nov., male; B. C. keralica sp. nov., male; C &amp; D. C. kodikanelensis Nielson, male and female; E. C. kumari sp. nov., male; F &amp; G. C. neofusca sp. nov., male and female; H &amp; I. C. ostenta (Distant), male and female; J. C. periyari sp. nov., male; K. C. subcrista Nielson, male; L. C. tridenta sp. nov., male; M. Glaberana acuta sp. nov., Male; N &amp; O. G. khasiensis (Rao), male and female. P. Glaberana purva sp. nov., male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366558/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">7 J</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="455F36E84A60E011FF5CFE09FF5EFD8D" blockId="12.[151,1437,261,936]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="7794EAFA4A60E011FF5CFE09FED4FE41" box="[199,372,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<collectingRegion id="8724F80A4A60E011FF5CFE09FEA1FE41" box="[199,257,405,431]" country="Maldives" name="Maale" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Male</collectingRegion>
genitalia.
</emphasis>
Pygofer with short ventral process, small lobe on caudodorsal margin (
<figureCitation id="DDDB2A6D4A60E011FB05FE09FAB0FE41" box="[1182,1296,405,431]" captionStart="FIGURES 21" captionStartId="56.[151,264,1965,1990]" captionTargetBox="[179,1395,193,1937]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[163,1423,166,1946]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURES 21 A–G. Calodia periyari sp. nov., male genitalia. A. Aedeagus, dorsal view; B &amp; C. Aedeagus, lateral view; D. Subgenital plate, dorsal view; E. Style, dorsal view; F. Connective, dorsal view; G. Pygofer, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366586/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 21 G</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate, long, slightly broader medially and slightly narrowed apically, with a few short, hair-like setae laterally (
<figureCitation id="DDDB2A6D4A60E011FAF4FE25FF71FE16" captionStart="FIGURES 21" captionStartId="56.[151,264,1965,1990]" captionTargetBox="[179,1395,193,1937]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[163,1423,166,1946]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURES 21 A–G. Calodia periyari sp. nov., male genitalia. A. Aedeagus, dorsal view; B &amp; C. Aedeagus, lateral view; D. Subgenital plate, dorsal view; E. Style, dorsal view; F. Connective, dorsal view; G. Pygofer, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366586/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 21 D</figureCitation>
). Style short and broad in basal ½ (
<figureCitation id="DDDB2A6D4A60E011FDC9FE41FD1CFE16" box="[594,700,477,504]" captionStart="FIGURES 21" captionStartId="56.[151,264,1965,1990]" captionTargetBox="[179,1395,193,1937]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[163,1423,166,1946]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURES 21 A–G. Calodia periyari sp. nov., male genitalia. A. Aedeagus, dorsal view; B &amp; C. Aedeagus, lateral view; D. Subgenital plate, dorsal view; E. Style, dorsal view; F. Connective, dorsal view; G. Pygofer, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366586/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 21 E</figureCitation>
). Connective as long as wide at base (
<figureCitation id="DDDB2A6D4A60E011FBC0FE41FB63FE16" box="[1115,1219,477,504]" captionStart="FIGURES 21" captionStartId="56.[151,264,1965,1990]" captionTargetBox="[179,1395,193,1937]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[163,1423,166,1946]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURES 21 A–G. Calodia periyari sp. nov., male genitalia. A. Aedeagus, dorsal view; B &amp; C. Aedeagus, lateral view; D. Subgenital plate, dorsal view; E. Style, dorsal view; F. Connective, dorsal view; G. Pygofer, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366586/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 21 F</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus slightly curved in distal 1/3, with two glabrous processes, distal process about 
<date id="315E10284A60E011FC3EFD9DFC61FDF5" box="[933,961,513,539]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">4x</date>
longer than the proximal process, bases of processes separated by a distance 
<date id="315E10284A60E011FD8AFDB9FD8DFDD1" box="[529,557,549,575]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">2x</date>
length of proximal process, gonopore arising distad of proximal process (
<figureCitation id="DDDB2A6D4A60E011FAFFFDB9FF13FD8D" captionStart="FIGURES 21" captionStartId="56.[151,264,1965,1990]" captionTargetBox="[179,1395,193,1937]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[163,1423,166,1946]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURES 21 A–G. Calodia periyari sp. nov., male genitalia. A. Aedeagus, dorsal view; B &amp; C. Aedeagus, lateral view; D. Subgenital plate, dorsal view; E. Style, dorsal view; F. Connective, dorsal view; G. Pygofer, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366586/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Figs. 21</figureCitation>
A–C).
</paragraph>
